Exactly! Here’s an example: you could do something like this:

```rust
// Cargo.toml dependency
// cfg-if = "1.0"

cfg_if::cfg_if! {
  if #[cfg(target_os = "linux")] {
    mod linux_impl;
    pub use linux_impl::*;
  } else if #[cfg(feature = "foo")] {
    mod foo;
    pub use foo::*;
  }
}
``` That way, your code is cleaner and easier to extend. And it’s idiomatic Rust.
